1
00:00:56,236 --> 00:00:59,073
FILING FOR LOVE

2
00:02:24,241 --> 00:02:26,326
EPISODE 5:
HEART BURN

3
00:02:45,971 --> 00:02:47,347
Miss.

4
00:02:48,849 --> 00:02:50,309
My heart was burning.

5
00:02:52,478 --> 00:02:53,687
I'm ready to pay.

6
00:02:53,771 --> 00:02:55,147
SOJU

7
00:02:55,230 --> 00:02:56,690
Miss.

8
00:02:56,774 --> 00:02:58,317
You'll die if you drink all this.

9
00:02:59,318 --> 00:03:00,360
That's the plan.

10
00:03:00,444 --> 00:03:03,030
Did something bad happen?

11
00:03:09,620 --> 00:03:10,954
I don't know

12
00:03:12,206 --> 00:03:13,582
what's happening.

13
00:03:23,175 --> 00:03:26,553
Hey, are you okay?
You're alive in there, right?

14
00:03:27,346 --> 00:03:29,139
How many hours
do you need to shower for?

15
00:03:52,037 --> 00:03:53,831
You could end up getting dehydrated.

16
00:03:58,460 --> 00:03:59,753
I'd like a beer, too.

17
00:04:07,678 --> 00:04:09,471
Why are you so flushed?

18
00:04:10,180 --> 00:04:11,723
Are you unwell?

19
00:04:12,140 --> 00:04:13,141
Is it a fever?

20
00:04:14,184 --> 00:04:15,769
You don't feel hot.

21
00:04:19,857 --> 00:04:21,024
I shouldn't flirt.

22
00:04:22,025 --> 00:04:23,861
I can't have you falling for me.

23
00:04:25,237 --> 00:04:26,989
Can it really happen?

24
00:04:27,531 --> 00:04:29,116
Can you really fall for someone

25
00:04:29,408 --> 00:04:31,869
you've known for so long?
Like you were hit by lightning.

26
00:04:31,952 --> 00:04:33,453
Did you really fall for me?

27
00:04:33,537 --> 00:04:35,455
That's only possible
if I were struck by lightning.

28
00:04:38,750 --> 00:04:40,586
Of course, it's possible.

29
00:04:41,253 --> 00:04:44,381
If you're given a reason
to see the person in a new light.

30
00:04:44,965 --> 00:04:47,843
Or it's possible
you'd already fallen for them.

31
00:04:48,510 --> 00:04:51,555
Before you knew it,
all your built-up feelings about them

32
00:04:51,638 --> 00:04:55,225
just blow up in an instant

33
00:04:55,893 --> 00:04:57,019
like lava.

34
00:04:58,604 --> 00:04:59,938
Like lava.

35
00:05:01,315 --> 00:05:03,859
J CONVALESCENT HOSPITAL

36
00:05:09,197 --> 00:05:10,282
Mother.

37
00:05:12,784 --> 00:05:14,119
The people here.

38
00:05:15,370 --> 00:05:17,205
They're not harassing you.

39
00:05:18,540 --> 00:05:19,875
They want to help you.

40
00:05:21,627 --> 00:05:23,754
If you refuse your medicine
and cause a fuss

41
00:05:25,589 --> 00:05:27,299
they'll send you back
to the psych ward.

42
00:05:35,974 --> 00:05:38,185
FATHER

43
00:05:45,859 --> 00:05:47,110
- Hello, Father.
- Where are you?

44
00:05:48,278 --> 00:05:49,529
I'm exercising.

45
00:05:49,613 --> 00:05:51,865
You have time for that?
What are you up to?

46
00:05:52,324 --> 00:05:54,451
You hired a fool like that
for that much money?

47
00:05:54,910 --> 00:05:56,828
If you did,
you must've put him to good use!

48
00:05:56,912 --> 00:05:58,205
Why did you cause trouble?

49
00:05:59,081 --> 00:06:00,123
HAEMU FIRES LOCKETT
FOR SEXUAL MISCONDUCT

50
00:06:00,207 --> 00:06:01,333
The Audit Team went after him.

51
00:06:01,541 --> 00:06:03,543
You still don't have control
of your own people?

52
00:06:04,002 --> 00:06:06,088
Who do you take after
to be this weak?

53
00:06:06,296 --> 00:06:07,965
Think about who you are
and what you are.

54
00:06:08,131 --> 00:06:10,217
If you can't handle it,
you'll crumble, just like your mom.

55
00:06:28,652 --> 00:06:30,320
Starting today, I want Joo In-a

56
00:06:30,904 --> 00:06:32,155
included in the executive updates.

57
00:06:32,239 --> 00:06:33,782
The Audit Team
keeps tabs on executives

58
00:06:33,865 --> 00:06:36,660
and report regularly,
so the Head isn't included in...

59
00:06:40,497 --> 00:06:41,748
I understand, sir.

60
00:06:41,832 --> 00:06:44,001
We'll keep tabs on her ourselves.

61
00:07:13,071 --> 00:07:14,531
Hello, Ms. Joo.

62
00:07:15,198 --> 00:07:16,700
Yes, hello. How are you?

63
00:07:17,034 --> 00:07:19,369
It was a pity
you missed the team dinner.

64
00:07:19,703 --> 00:07:22,330
It was.
Let's hope there's a next time.

65
00:07:22,456 --> 00:07:23,498
How about

66
00:07:23,999 --> 00:07:26,251
you and I grab a drink?

67
00:07:26,334 --> 00:07:27,753
Just you and me.

68
00:07:30,964 --> 00:07:33,425
I don't see how you'd enjoy
joining me for a drink.

69
00:07:33,675 --> 00:07:34,843
We have nothing in common.

70
00:07:34,926 --> 00:07:36,636
There might be something.

71
00:07:37,012 --> 00:07:40,432
You and I could have
something surprising in common.

72
00:08:16,968 --> 00:08:18,220
Morning.

73
00:08:18,512 --> 00:08:21,223
Let's have a coffee.
We need to talk, too.

74
00:08:23,100 --> 00:08:24,184
Forget the coffee.

75
00:08:24,768 --> 00:08:26,561
We can talk in the interview room.

76
00:09:09,771 --> 00:09:11,982
- Yesterday...
- Sorry about that. I apologize.

77
00:09:13,066 --> 00:09:15,360
I shouldn't have done that
as your superior.

78
00:09:16,236 --> 00:09:17,988
If you want to lodge
an official complaint

79
00:09:18,697 --> 00:09:19,698
then go ahead.

80
00:09:20,157 --> 00:09:21,992
I'll admit and accept everything.

81
00:09:24,286 --> 00:09:26,496
You seem to be gravely mistaken.

82
00:09:27,706 --> 00:09:29,040
I kissed you.

83
00:09:30,792 --> 00:09:33,128
What are you talking about?
I'm the one who kissed you.

84
00:09:33,211 --> 00:09:35,422
I kissed you, Ms. Joo.

85
00:09:35,797 --> 00:09:37,340
Don't argue with me. I started it.

86
00:09:37,424 --> 00:09:39,676
I'm not arguing.
Do you think you used

87
00:09:39,759 --> 00:09:41,094
your rank or authority
to pressure me?

88
00:09:42,512 --> 00:09:45,015
Why are you trying to subdue me?

89
00:09:45,098 --> 00:09:46,975
- I'm saying I did what I did.
- I did it.

90
00:09:47,058 --> 00:09:49,060
- I did it.
- Why?

91
00:09:52,898 --> 00:09:54,482
Why did you kiss me?

92
00:09:55,483 --> 00:09:56,735
That is, if you did it.

93
00:09:59,863 --> 00:10:00,906
I was intoxicated

94
00:10:01,698 --> 00:10:02,782
with art.

95
00:10:03,200 --> 00:10:06,119
You're a great artist.
Your work was just beautiful.

96
00:10:06,203 --> 00:10:09,247
Not to mention the calm music
playing in the background.

97
00:10:09,331 --> 00:10:11,666
There was something about the moment
and its atmosphere.

98
00:10:12,334 --> 00:10:13,543
It was intoxicating.

99
00:10:13,835 --> 00:10:15,212
There's a scientific rationale.

100
00:10:15,295 --> 00:10:18,006
A great work of art
stimulates dopamine secretion

101
00:10:18,089 --> 00:10:20,926
which arouses you,
accelerating your pulse and breath.

102
00:10:23,011 --> 00:10:24,346
Like you're under a magic spell.

103
00:10:33,480 --> 00:10:35,106
Was what I drew that good?

104
00:10:35,899 --> 00:10:37,734
Do you think
I'm Michelangelo or something?

105
00:10:38,568 --> 00:10:40,654
I should call you Noh-chelangelo.

106
00:10:43,990 --> 00:10:46,201
The excuse you came up with
was that art intoxicated you?

107
00:10:46,326 --> 00:10:47,410
That's all there is to it?

108
00:10:49,037 --> 00:10:50,330
What about you, then?

109
00:10:50,580 --> 00:10:52,958
Why did you kiss me?
That is, if you did it first.

110
00:10:57,963 --> 00:10:59,047
You were pretty.

111
00:11:01,091 --> 00:11:03,301
I was stone-cold sober
and in my right mind.

112
00:11:04,135 --> 00:11:05,804
I just found you pretty.

113
00:11:08,556 --> 00:11:09,683
That's why I kissed you.

114
00:11:20,068 --> 00:11:21,236
I've always been pretty.

115
00:11:22,821 --> 00:11:24,698
Anyone would say so.
I have nice facial features

116
00:11:24,781 --> 00:11:26,157
and they're in the right place.

117
00:11:26,241 --> 00:11:27,367
I have an objectively pretty face.

118
00:11:27,784 --> 00:11:28,868
So what?

119
00:11:29,286 --> 00:11:31,621
That doesn't mean
every man kisses me.

120
00:11:37,627 --> 00:11:38,878
Regardless of who started it

121
00:11:39,379 --> 00:11:42,299
we have to admit what happened
yesterday wasn't normal.

122
00:11:43,091 --> 00:11:44,634
To make sure
this doesn't happen again

123
00:11:44,718 --> 00:11:47,429
let's keep a reasonable distance
for risk management purposes.

124
00:11:47,512 --> 00:11:49,931
We should keep our work
and private lives separate, too. Bye.

125
00:11:58,523 --> 00:12:01,192
Just so you know,
it's really annoying.

126
00:12:02,652 --> 00:12:03,903
Kissing and then apologizing for it.

127
00:12:11,369 --> 00:12:13,621
Mr. Cha, born in 1988,
Year of the Dragon.

128
00:12:13,705 --> 00:12:15,290
Your daily fortune says...

129
00:12:16,082 --> 00:12:18,877
Oh, you should organize
your surroundings.

130
00:12:18,960 --> 00:12:22,464
Hae-young, born in 1989,
Year of the Snake.

131
00:12:24,132 --> 00:12:26,760
Gosh. Someone special
will come from the west.

132
00:12:27,010 --> 00:12:28,470
- The west?
- Ms. Pyun.

133
00:12:28,762 --> 00:12:30,305
I live in Bucheon in the west.

134
00:12:31,097 --> 00:12:32,182
Am I special to you?

135
00:12:33,183 --> 00:12:36,019
Mr. Moo with the Year of the Ram.

136
00:12:37,228 --> 00:12:39,981
Try not to get noticed
by your superior.

137
00:12:40,065 --> 00:12:41,483
- My superior?
- Your superior.

138
00:12:44,027 --> 00:12:45,153
Where is she?

139
00:12:46,196 --> 00:12:48,031
- What's up?
- Shoot.

140
00:12:48,531 --> 00:12:50,992
Oh, dear, gosh.

141
00:12:51,368 --> 00:12:53,036
The economy has changed a great deal.

142
00:12:53,119 --> 00:12:55,497
What's the world coming to?

143
00:12:56,831 --> 00:12:59,250
What do you think is up
with those two this morning?

144
00:12:59,334 --> 00:13:01,628
Mr. Noh has always been
in Ms. Joo's bad books.

145
00:13:01,711 --> 00:13:04,297
I thought things had improved
while working on James's case.

146
00:13:04,381 --> 00:13:06,049
What if things
go really badly for Mr. Noh

147
00:13:06,549 --> 00:13:08,134
and chaos comes for him?

148
00:13:08,218 --> 00:13:11,846
I have a feeling we should step up
and help him out

149
00:13:11,930 --> 00:13:14,557
so the two can get closer.
Oh, my gosh.

150
00:13:14,641 --> 00:13:18,019
Oh, dear. AI.
Artificial Intelligence...

151
00:13:18,478 --> 00:13:19,479
It's just...

152
00:13:27,028 --> 00:13:28,613
I'm so jealous of him.

153
00:13:29,072 --> 00:13:30,865
This is his lucky year.

154
00:13:30,949 --> 00:13:34,494
He got married and was named
Haemu Cosmetics' King of Sales.

155
00:13:34,619 --> 00:13:36,996
It's not the first time
he won that title.

156
00:13:37,414 --> 00:13:38,748
The punk.

157
00:13:38,998 --> 00:13:41,584
I begged him to share
his trade secret, but he won't.

158
00:13:41,668 --> 00:13:44,170
- Let's go outside for a smoke.
- Sure.

159
00:14:07,944 --> 00:14:09,487
Are you all ready?

160
00:14:09,571 --> 00:14:12,031
One, two, three.

161
00:14:26,087 --> 00:14:27,380
What the heck's going on?

162
00:14:28,089 --> 00:14:29,132
What is she doing?

163
00:14:29,799 --> 00:14:30,842
Hands off me!

164
00:14:37,307 --> 00:14:40,643
I have no relationship whatsoever
with that woman.

165
00:14:41,311 --> 00:14:44,105
She's the head buyer
at one of our clients.

166
00:14:44,189 --> 00:14:45,940
I'm a salesman at her mercy.

167
00:14:46,024 --> 00:14:47,734
She's the buyer in control.

168
00:14:48,401 --> 00:14:49,486
That's it.

169
00:14:49,569 --> 00:14:52,864
But she caused a ruckus
at your wedding for no good reason?

170
00:14:52,947 --> 00:14:54,115
Exactly.

171
00:14:54,199 --> 00:14:56,701
How confused and rattled
do you think I was?

172
00:14:56,993 --> 00:14:59,871
If we had even a situationship,
I wouldn't have invited her.

173
00:14:59,954 --> 00:15:01,414
I'm not that crazy.

174
00:15:02,999 --> 00:15:04,584
Bros, this is totally unfair.

175
00:15:04,667 --> 00:15:06,753
We're not your bros, Mr. Do.

176
00:15:07,253 --> 00:15:09,839
Sit up straight.
We're not here to fool around.

177
00:15:10,173 --> 00:15:11,424
Sorry.

178
00:15:11,841 --> 00:15:13,801
Anyway,
there really isn't much to it.

179
00:15:14,719 --> 00:15:16,763
That's why even after that disaster
at my wedding

180
00:15:17,013 --> 00:15:18,556
I'm enjoying my newlywed life.

181
00:15:18,890 --> 00:15:21,768
There must be a reason she acted out.

182
00:15:22,268 --> 00:15:24,938
Did you give her reason to think
there was something between you?

183
00:15:28,816 --> 00:15:29,859
Well, actually...

184
00:15:30,693 --> 00:15:33,029
I've actually got
a sales tactic of my own.

185
00:15:34,405 --> 00:15:37,408
I sell lipsticks for a living.

186
00:15:37,617 --> 00:15:39,327
Most of the buyers are women.

187
00:15:39,410 --> 00:15:42,080
When a man and a woman work together

188
00:15:42,163 --> 00:15:44,374
there's bound to be
a little sexual chemistry.

189
00:15:44,457 --> 00:15:47,168
I use that as best I can
to make a sale.

190
00:15:47,502 --> 00:15:50,755
Are you saying you get your way
by using your physique somehow?

191
00:15:51,130 --> 00:15:54,217
Gosh, no, bro... Mr. Cha.

192
00:15:56,844 --> 00:15:58,721
Flirting. That's it.

193
00:15:58,972 --> 00:16:01,891
One, do just enough. Two, be polite.

194
00:16:01,975 --> 00:16:05,019
But how? You make the lady feel good.

195
00:16:05,478 --> 00:16:07,772
You create a thrill and tension.

196
00:16:07,855 --> 00:16:10,900
I prey on their emotions
without crossing the line.

197
00:16:11,859 --> 00:16:14,487
They usually know what's happening
and play along.

198
00:16:15,530 --> 00:16:18,116
Is Ms. So a bit delusional?

199
00:16:21,369 --> 00:16:23,079
We were definitely dating.

200
00:16:26,541 --> 00:16:29,627
You don't have to say,
"We're now officially together."

201
00:16:29,877 --> 00:16:32,213
There comes a moment
when you just know

202
00:16:32,630 --> 00:16:34,465
that you have something special.

203
00:16:34,591 --> 00:16:36,050
I was confused at first.

204
00:16:36,134 --> 00:16:39,137
I thought he was being nice
just to increase his sales.

205
00:16:46,477 --> 00:16:48,938
Oh, dear. Are you that ill?

206
00:16:49,022 --> 00:16:51,482
I said I was unwell, and he brought
porridge and medicine

207
00:16:51,566 --> 00:16:53,151
in the middle of the night.

208
00:16:54,027 --> 00:16:57,322
That's something you do
when you actually care about someone.

209
00:16:57,405 --> 00:16:58,656
Dress warmly.

210
00:16:58,740 --> 00:17:00,700
Yes, that's usually true.

211
00:17:00,783 --> 00:17:01,826
But in that case...

212
00:17:02,619 --> 00:17:05,413
I needed her to settle the bill,
and she said she was too sick.

213
00:17:05,997 --> 00:17:08,166
What else could I do
but try to make her feel better?

214
00:17:09,167 --> 00:17:12,378
I went to a nearby pharmacy
and bought all the strongest meds.

215
00:17:12,462 --> 00:17:14,339
- This must be taken warm.
- That, too?

216
00:17:14,422 --> 00:17:15,506
She loved the attention.

217
00:17:15,590 --> 00:17:18,051
- She wired the money the next day.
- Get well soon.

218
00:17:19,761 --> 00:17:22,305
So I accepted his date request.

219
00:17:23,306 --> 00:17:26,059
- Hello.
- We watched a movie and ate out.

220
00:17:26,476 --> 00:17:28,353
It was an ordinary weekend date.

221
00:17:29,145 --> 00:17:31,731
A date?
So that's what she thought it was.

222
00:17:33,399 --> 00:17:36,653
"I'm bored on weekends.
I roll around at home all day long."

223
00:17:36,736 --> 00:17:39,530
She kept whining, so I sent her
movie tickets the company gives us.

224
00:17:39,614 --> 00:17:41,240
When she got them...

225
00:17:41,991 --> 00:17:43,618
She said she was only free
that Saturday.

226
00:17:43,701 --> 00:17:46,746
It felt like I was going to work
on a weekend.

227
00:17:47,538 --> 00:17:48,873
"Going to work"?

228
00:17:49,666 --> 00:17:52,585
He never stopped saying
I was cute or pretty

229
00:17:53,294 --> 00:17:56,297
and wiped my lips
when I got food on my face.

230
00:17:57,423 --> 00:17:58,758
Is that part of his job description?

231
00:18:01,302 --> 00:18:02,428
Take a look.

232
00:18:04,472 --> 00:18:07,850
He texts me, "Good morning"
and "Good night"

233
00:18:07,934 --> 00:18:09,560
every single day without fail.

234
00:18:10,520 --> 00:18:12,021
And this means nothing?

235
00:18:12,939 --> 00:18:15,525
Let us take a look at that.

236
00:18:16,526 --> 00:18:17,777
Let's scroll up.

237
00:18:19,278 --> 00:18:20,905
OKAY, I'LL EMAIL IT TO YOU!

238
00:18:20,988 --> 00:18:22,240
GOOD NIGHT, SEE YOU TOMORROW

239
00:18:23,908 --> 00:18:25,284
I see your point.

240
00:18:26,994 --> 00:18:28,037
Thanks.

241
00:18:28,705 --> 00:18:30,164
The thing is...

242
00:18:31,207 --> 00:18:33,126
We checked Mr. Do's phone as well.

243
00:18:34,293 --> 00:18:37,004
He texts the same thing
to all his clients.

244
00:18:37,463 --> 00:18:39,632
It's practically copied and pasted.

245
00:18:41,175 --> 00:18:42,343
Copied and pasted?

246
00:18:44,053 --> 00:18:45,263
He's a psycho.

247
00:18:45,346 --> 00:18:48,641
Do you have another clearer incident

248
00:18:49,100 --> 00:18:52,186
that could help
prove your relationship?

249
00:18:55,440 --> 00:18:56,607
The kiss.

250
00:18:58,568 --> 00:19:00,403
He and I kissed.

251
00:19:01,446 --> 00:19:02,655
"Kiss"?

252
00:19:05,408 --> 00:19:07,910
This is just madness.

253
00:19:08,536 --> 00:19:11,330
I'm a guy who never crosses a line.

254
00:19:11,664 --> 00:19:13,541
Physical touch? Never.

255
00:19:13,624 --> 00:19:15,251
You brought her medicine at night

256
00:19:15,334 --> 00:19:17,003
went to a movie together
and texted each other

257
00:19:17,378 --> 00:19:20,214
- but you didn't kiss?
- We didn't. Never.

258
00:19:26,387 --> 00:19:28,639
Why did you stop the investigation
halfway through?

259
00:19:29,015 --> 00:19:31,267
You called a client over
for questioning

260
00:19:31,851 --> 00:19:33,311
and you don't conclude your report?

261
00:19:33,394 --> 00:19:36,022
It's a personal issue
between the two of them.

262
00:19:36,105 --> 00:19:38,399
They have different opinions
about one incident.

263
00:19:38,483 --> 00:19:40,234
How can we check that objectively?

264
00:19:40,735 --> 00:19:42,236
Don't you know the saying

265
00:19:42,320 --> 00:19:44,989
the truth between two people
isn't with just one

266
00:19:45,114 --> 00:19:46,783
but it exists
on the periphery of both.

267
00:19:46,866 --> 00:19:48,993
Then you must check the periphery.

268
00:19:49,076 --> 00:19:50,995
They clearly disagree on one matter.

269
00:19:51,078 --> 00:19:53,247
Ms. So says they kissed.
Mr. Do says they didn't.

270
00:19:53,331 --> 00:19:54,624
Isn't that an important point?

271
00:19:55,750 --> 00:19:58,252
If Mr. Do is denying kissing her

272
00:19:58,336 --> 00:20:01,255
that could be sexual harassment,
and it could hurt business ties.

273
00:20:01,380 --> 00:20:03,925
Not to mention
it's incredibly rude to the lady.

274
00:20:06,552 --> 00:20:07,887
I see.

275
00:20:08,721 --> 00:20:10,556
Is that how important a kiss is?

276
00:20:12,683 --> 00:20:14,018
Even after the kiss

277
00:20:15,603 --> 00:20:17,855
I thought an apology
would settle everything.

278
00:20:23,361 --> 00:20:24,779
Let's stick to work.

279
00:20:26,322 --> 00:20:27,532
Where did they kiss?

280
00:20:33,037 --> 00:20:34,789
It was after they ate here.

281
00:20:38,751 --> 00:20:40,753
Describe the situation in detail.

282
00:20:40,837 --> 00:20:43,005
Do your job properly, Mr. Noh.

283
00:20:55,309 --> 00:20:58,437
They left after having
a few cocktails at the bar upstairs.

284
00:20:58,521 --> 00:21:01,274
Ms. So can't drink much,
so she was very drunk.

285
00:21:01,357 --> 00:21:03,150
She could barely walk.

286
00:21:03,484 --> 00:21:04,652
And then...

287
00:21:16,163 --> 00:21:17,707
I feel dizzy.

288
00:21:19,166 --> 00:21:20,209
Oh, my gosh.

289
00:21:22,295 --> 00:21:25,840
So Mr. Do helped Ms. So
stand up straight.

290
00:21:29,635 --> 00:21:31,304
They stood here, facing each other.

291
00:21:47,403 --> 00:21:49,238
There's no need
to reenact the whole thing.

292
00:21:49,488 --> 00:21:51,032
You told me to go into detail.

293
00:21:51,115 --> 00:21:52,408
You're contradicting yourself.

294
00:21:56,037 --> 00:21:58,039
There's a camera up there.
Let's get the footage.

295
00:21:58,748 --> 00:22:00,291
It looks like a fake.

296
00:22:03,836 --> 00:22:04,837
How can you tell?

297
00:22:05,171 --> 00:22:06,213
Look carefully.

298
00:22:07,298 --> 00:22:09,300
There are no electrical wires

299
00:22:09,550 --> 00:22:10,718
or blinking light.

300
00:22:12,595 --> 00:22:13,930
It's cold to the touch.

301
00:22:14,388 --> 00:22:16,307
I bet it never worked.

302
00:22:16,724 --> 00:22:19,977
Hey, Mr. Noh. You have your uses.

303
00:22:27,693 --> 00:22:30,071
There should be a camera or two here.

304
00:22:37,912 --> 00:22:39,246
ROTISSERIE CHICKEN

305
00:22:49,566 --> 00:22:52,402
So, did the DOJ meeting happen?

306
00:22:53,361 --> 00:22:55,321
I heard JB pulled some strings.

307
00:22:55,405 --> 00:22:56,906
You jerk.

308
00:22:57,198 --> 00:22:59,867
You invited me out to practice
just to discuss work?

309
00:23:03,413 --> 00:23:06,666
Sir. It's Managing Director Jeon.
What shall I do?

310
00:23:06,749 --> 00:23:08,835
- Say I'll call him back.
- Yes, sir.

311
00:23:16,384 --> 00:23:18,511
Isn't she a looker? Can you focus?

312
00:23:18,595 --> 00:23:20,680
She's smart and thorough.

313
00:23:20,763 --> 00:23:22,098
You're so uptight.

314
00:23:22,181 --> 00:23:24,350
I understand.

315
00:23:24,726 --> 00:23:26,853
You need someone to talk to.

316
00:23:28,938 --> 00:23:32,025
I get that your marriage was
a business deal, but your wife...

317
00:23:33,776 --> 00:23:35,862
I couldn't live with her
even if my dad threatened to kill me.

318
00:23:41,951 --> 00:23:44,162
- Hello, sir.
- Hi there.

319
00:23:44,245 --> 00:23:45,997
The chicken looks amazing.

320
00:23:46,080 --> 00:23:49,167
They're so plump, I thought
they were turkeys from over there.

321
00:23:49,917 --> 00:23:51,461
They taste just as good, too.

322
00:23:51,544 --> 00:23:54,255
Mr. Noh. Isn't it mesmerizing
to watch them turn?

323
00:23:54,339 --> 00:23:56,841
I wish I could do that to you
whenever you get on my nerves.

324
00:23:57,800 --> 00:23:59,510
Oh, you like to truss people up?

325
00:24:02,805 --> 00:24:05,892
Sir, how many times a week
do you come here?

326
00:24:05,975 --> 00:24:08,019
I'm here every day apart from Sunday.

327
00:24:08,102 --> 00:24:09,354
Oh, really?

328
00:24:09,854 --> 00:24:14,192
Do you park your truck
at this angle whenever you're here?

329
00:24:15,526 --> 00:24:16,653
What?

330
00:24:16,736 --> 00:24:20,365
Do you park your truck
like this every time?

331
00:24:24,285 --> 00:24:26,579
It smells amazing.

332
00:24:26,663 --> 00:24:29,248
Take this home
and share with your family.

333
00:24:29,332 --> 00:24:30,541
You have a big family.

334
00:24:30,625 --> 00:24:33,211
We live separately now.

335
00:24:33,294 --> 00:24:35,213
Do you live on your own, then?

336
00:24:35,672 --> 00:24:36,714
Yes.

337
00:24:44,597 --> 00:24:45,682
Hello?

338
00:24:50,395 --> 00:24:51,938
You got the wrong number.

339
00:24:59,320 --> 00:25:00,613
Who was that?

340
00:25:01,364 --> 00:25:02,615
A wrong number.

341
00:25:04,033 --> 00:25:05,284
Let's take a look.

342
00:25:06,160 --> 00:25:07,870
We got the perfect angle.

343
00:25:07,954 --> 00:25:09,163
Press rewind.

344
00:25:09,706 --> 00:25:10,998
We must go back

345
00:25:11,708 --> 00:25:13,960
to between 10 p.m. and midnight.

346
00:25:16,838 --> 00:25:18,214
There they are.

347
00:25:40,570 --> 00:25:42,697
Gosh, they actually kissed.

348
00:25:54,792 --> 00:25:57,295
Mr. Choi got a call
that his second kid was hurt.

349
00:25:57,378 --> 00:25:58,755
I told him to go home.

350
00:25:58,838 --> 00:26:01,257
Good for you. Tell him to take
as long as he needs off work.

351
00:26:01,340 --> 00:26:02,550
Yes, sir.

352
00:26:03,217 --> 00:26:04,844
I'll drive you home tonight.

353
00:26:06,721 --> 00:26:08,806
It's fine. I'll drive.

354
00:26:14,187 --> 00:26:15,271
Bye, then.

355
00:26:19,650 --> 00:26:20,651
Ms. Park.

356
00:26:24,906 --> 00:26:26,199
Where did you move to?

357
00:26:45,760 --> 00:26:47,303
You can drop me off here.

358
00:26:54,811 --> 00:26:55,937
Thank you, sir.

359
00:26:57,563 --> 00:26:58,648
Ms. Park.

360
00:26:59,232 --> 00:27:00,858
From now on, Mr. Choi or Do-young

361
00:27:01,484 --> 00:27:03,277
will accompany me
on my personal business.

362
00:27:03,903 --> 00:27:06,489
I'd like you to concentrate
on work-related tasks.

363
00:27:11,285 --> 00:27:12,787
You don't have to do that

364
00:27:13,538 --> 00:27:16,457
if it's because my feelings
are making you uncomfortable.

365
00:27:19,544 --> 00:27:20,795
I live

366
00:27:21,712 --> 00:27:22,839
with a guy right now.

367
00:27:24,966 --> 00:27:26,634
He's a really nice guy.

368
00:27:28,135 --> 00:27:30,638
So there's no need for you to worry.

369
00:27:32,807 --> 00:27:35,017
I won't get all clingy.

370
00:27:40,898 --> 00:27:42,525
Speak of the devil.

371
00:27:43,860 --> 00:27:45,778
I'll see you tomorrow, sir.

372
00:28:02,420 --> 00:28:03,546
What's this about?

373
00:28:05,756 --> 00:28:06,841
Sorry.

374
00:28:07,592 --> 00:28:09,510
I used you for something.

375
00:28:09,594 --> 00:28:10,970
- Was that a guy?
- It's a secret.

376
00:28:11,512 --> 00:28:13,598
What do you want for dinner?
My treat.

377
00:28:14,098 --> 00:28:15,641
Why does everyone have a secret?

378
00:28:15,725 --> 00:28:18,477
- Who else has a secret?
- That's my secret, okay?

379
00:28:33,534 --> 00:28:36,162
Doesn't that clear up

380
00:28:36,537 --> 00:28:37,830
what our relationship was?

381
00:28:38,581 --> 00:28:40,958
Doesn't a kiss make it official?

382
00:28:41,959 --> 00:28:44,837
Do you two kiss someone
you're not dating?

383
00:28:45,254 --> 00:28:47,798
Am I the old-fashioned one here?

384
00:28:48,716 --> 00:28:52,261
I mean, if you kiss someone,
doesn't that mean

385
00:28:52,345 --> 00:28:56,307
you have a kind of relationship
that you should be responsible for?

386
00:28:56,641 --> 00:28:57,975
Yes, sure.

387
00:28:58,976 --> 00:29:01,646
But according to Mr. Do...

388
00:29:02,813 --> 00:29:04,106
We kissed?

389
00:29:05,483 --> 00:29:08,778
Now that I think about it,
maybe we did.

390
00:29:09,362 --> 00:29:10,863
I must've been too drunk.

391
00:29:11,697 --> 00:29:14,700
That could also mean
how insignificant it was to me.

392
00:29:15,201 --> 00:29:16,994
She wouldn't stop hitting on me

393
00:29:17,078 --> 00:29:18,496
so while we were drunk...

394
00:29:19,205 --> 00:29:20,414
You know what I mean.

395
00:29:23,793 --> 00:29:27,380
I'm old enough to know how things are

396
00:29:28,506 --> 00:29:29,715
and I'm not stupid.

397
00:29:30,383 --> 00:29:33,260
A momentary mistake
and an emotional connection?

398
00:29:33,344 --> 00:29:36,555
I can definitely make
the distinction very clearly.

399
00:29:39,517 --> 00:29:40,726
You're right.

400
00:29:41,936 --> 00:29:44,230
They're different. I'm not...

401
00:29:44,981 --> 00:29:47,274
You're not old-fashioned, Ms. So.

402
00:29:47,358 --> 00:29:50,152
We know enough
to be able to tell the difference.

403
00:29:50,236 --> 00:29:52,029
Yes, that's it.

404
00:29:52,530 --> 00:29:54,240
What, a mistake?

405
00:29:55,074 --> 00:29:57,868
He can't remember the kiss?
Does he have amnesia?

406
00:29:57,952 --> 00:29:59,954
Did the kiss happen
with only one person?

407
00:30:00,037 --> 00:30:01,414
Why is everything one-sided?

408
00:30:01,497 --> 00:30:03,666
I haven't made sense of it
at all yet.

409
00:30:03,749 --> 00:30:06,168
The other person concluded
like it was nothing.

410
00:30:06,252 --> 00:30:07,503
Right?

411
00:30:07,837 --> 00:30:10,589
So what? It doesn't change anything.

412
00:30:11,549 --> 00:30:13,718
Not all people who kiss are dating.

413
00:30:13,968 --> 00:30:16,470
In some countries,
a kiss is just a greeting.

414
00:30:17,263 --> 00:30:18,556
Do I have to

415
00:30:19,682 --> 00:30:21,434
marry someone just because we kissed?

416
00:30:25,187 --> 00:30:27,523
A kiss definitely makes it official.

417
00:30:28,733 --> 00:30:30,443
You kiss because you're dating

418
00:30:30,526 --> 00:30:32,028
and you date because you kissed.

419
00:30:32,403 --> 00:30:33,904
Our ancestors back in the day

420
00:30:33,988 --> 00:30:37,575
had to take responsibility
and marry someone they talked to.

421
00:30:37,658 --> 00:30:39,285
How far back in time are you going?

422
00:30:39,577 --> 00:30:42,538
These days, you sleep before you date
and go to bed first before going out.

423
00:30:42,830 --> 00:30:43,873
Sleep before what?

424
00:30:43,956 --> 00:30:46,083
You sleep with the partner first
before you start dating them.

425
00:30:46,459 --> 00:30:49,211
And you take someone to bed first
before taking them out.

426
00:30:50,629 --> 00:30:53,132
But aren't kisses a bit different?

427
00:30:53,340 --> 00:30:55,968
There's an old film
called Pretty Woman.

428
00:30:56,552 --> 00:30:58,345
In that film, Julia Roberts

429
00:30:58,429 --> 00:31:01,599
does just about everything
with Richard Gere

430
00:31:02,641 --> 00:31:05,269
but says,
"I don't kiss on the mouth."

431
00:31:06,145 --> 00:31:08,647
Why? Because kissing

432
00:31:08,731 --> 00:31:11,150
is more emotionally charged
than sleeping with someone.

433
00:31:11,817 --> 00:31:14,528
I don't particularly like Mr. Do

434
00:31:14,612 --> 00:31:16,864
but I believe
people can make drunken mistakes.

435
00:31:17,490 --> 00:31:22,203
I mean, getting physical
doesn't always equal a relationship.

436
00:31:22,286 --> 00:31:23,329
I don't know.

437
00:31:23,579 --> 00:31:25,456
We'll have to figure out
the situation before and after

438
00:31:25,539 --> 00:31:27,500
but what bothers me
is the fact that Mr. Do lied.

439
00:31:27,583 --> 00:31:31,253
It's the proof that shows
their kiss must've been significant.

440
00:31:31,337 --> 00:31:34,465
If it really meant nothing,
and he has a clear conscience

441
00:31:34,548 --> 00:31:35,591
he should've admitted to it.

442
00:31:36,342 --> 00:31:37,468
Hey, you're right.

443
00:31:38,094 --> 00:31:40,012
That's true. At times

444
00:31:40,721 --> 00:31:43,182
the truth is hidden between the lies.

445
00:31:44,892 --> 00:31:46,519
- Ms. Joo!
- Goodness.

446
00:31:47,978 --> 00:31:49,605
We put this together for you

447
00:31:49,688 --> 00:31:51,148
so make sure
you smooth things over with her.

448
00:31:51,232 --> 00:31:53,025
Kiss up to her and humor her.

449
00:31:53,109 --> 00:31:55,152
- Goodness. This way, please.
- You're all here.

450
00:31:57,279 --> 00:31:58,656
I'll just sit here.

451
00:31:58,739 --> 00:32:00,699
But I set up everything for you

452
00:32:00,783 --> 00:32:01,992
and warmed up the seat.

453
00:32:04,370 --> 00:32:06,205
I see. All right, then.

454
00:32:06,288 --> 00:32:07,665
This way, please.

455
00:32:13,295 --> 00:32:15,131
And a new glass for you.

456
00:32:15,214 --> 00:32:16,507
- Thank you.
- Sure.

457
00:32:20,970 --> 00:32:22,096
Mr. Noh.

458
00:32:22,596 --> 00:32:24,974
What are you waiting for?
She's here. Pour her a drink.

459
00:32:35,526 --> 00:32:37,862
What were you all chatting about?

460
00:32:37,945 --> 00:32:40,739
I saw a few of you
giving a whole speech as I walked in.

461
00:32:40,823 --> 00:32:42,241
It was this.

462
00:32:43,117 --> 00:32:46,120
Ms. Joo.
Kissing equals dating, right?

463
00:32:48,622 --> 00:32:49,623
What?

464
00:32:54,086 --> 00:32:55,129
What do you mean?

465
00:33:01,010 --> 00:33:03,470
You were talking about Mr. Do!

466
00:33:04,096 --> 00:33:07,266
Why are you discussing work
at a team dinner? You workaholics!

467
00:33:07,975 --> 00:33:09,810
Forget that.
Let's talk about something else.

468
00:33:09,894 --> 00:33:11,520
Why? It was just getting fun.

469
00:33:11,979 --> 00:33:14,648
It's not fun to talk about work
while drinking.

470
00:33:15,524 --> 00:33:18,152
- Now, why don't we make a toast?
- Sure.

471
00:33:18,235 --> 00:33:20,487
Fill up your glasses.

472
00:33:20,779 --> 00:33:22,281
Thank you.

473
00:33:22,364 --> 00:33:25,284
For the workaholics
of Audit Team Three.

474
00:33:25,367 --> 00:33:27,786
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

475
00:33:40,633 --> 00:33:42,843
- Are you okay?
- I'm fine. I'm okay.

476
00:33:43,427 --> 00:33:46,096
So do you want to grab
one more drink?

477
00:33:46,555 --> 00:33:49,725
Your team should let loose
without me in round two

478
00:33:49,808 --> 00:33:51,227
so you can talk behind my back.

479
00:33:51,310 --> 00:33:53,270
Goodness, don't say
something like that.

480
00:33:53,354 --> 00:33:56,315
All of us, especially Mr. Noh

481
00:33:56,398 --> 00:33:59,902
adore and respect you so much,
Ms. Joo.

482
00:33:59,985 --> 00:34:05,449
He's right. Ms. Joo, you are
the coolest boss in the world.

483
00:34:05,532 --> 00:34:06,825
He's drunk.

484
00:34:07,034 --> 00:34:08,285
Mr. Baek.

485
00:34:08,369 --> 00:34:10,663
You once said I wasn't good enough

486
00:34:10,746 --> 00:34:13,082
and that I should
draw the line for the team.

487
00:34:13,165 --> 00:34:16,043
Didn't you look at me like this
and get angry at me?

488
00:34:16,460 --> 00:34:19,713
Well, back then,
I didn't know any better.

489
00:34:19,797 --> 00:34:22,466
But Ms. Joo, you really know

490
00:34:22,549 --> 00:34:24,885
how to draw the perfect line!

491
00:34:29,139 --> 00:34:30,266
Mr. Noh.

492
00:34:30,641 --> 00:34:33,519
You should be good to Ms. Joo, okay?

493
00:34:35,646 --> 00:34:38,232
Goodness.
It's time for you to go home.

494
00:34:38,315 --> 00:34:39,608
- My gosh.
- Careful.

495
00:34:39,984 --> 00:34:42,695
All right, then.
We should call it a night.

496
00:34:42,778 --> 00:34:44,363
Okay. Wait, Mr. Noh.

497
00:34:44,446 --> 00:34:47,199
You should grab a cab for Ms. Joo.
It's quite late.

498
00:34:47,283 --> 00:34:49,201
- No, it's all right.
- It's not all right!

499
00:34:49,285 --> 00:34:51,203
Make sure you grab it for her.
Do that, okay?

500
00:34:51,287 --> 00:34:53,664
- See you tomorrow!
- See you tomorrow!

501
00:34:53,747 --> 00:34:56,625
- Sure. Have a safe trip back home.
- Mr. Moo.

502
00:34:57,876 --> 00:35:00,170
What? No, I can't do that.
It's too late.

503
00:35:00,254 --> 00:35:01,797
- The night is still young.
- No.

504
00:35:03,215 --> 00:35:05,301
They think I hate you, don't they?

505
00:35:06,593 --> 00:35:08,554
You have the best teammates.

506
00:35:09,513 --> 00:35:10,889
They're good people.

507
00:35:13,100 --> 00:35:14,310
So...

508
00:35:16,520 --> 00:35:17,980
it sounds like you don't hate me.

509
00:35:40,127 --> 00:35:42,296
Hey, there's my cab.
See you tomorrow.

510
00:35:44,214 --> 00:35:47,384
VACANT

511
00:35:49,595 --> 00:35:51,680
- To AL Tower, please.
- Sure.

512
00:35:58,020 --> 00:36:00,189
- Sir, please start driving.
- What are you doing?

513
00:36:03,150 --> 00:36:04,860
It's late, so I thought
I'd bring you home.

514
00:36:05,361 --> 00:36:07,029
You saw me get in the cab,
and that's good enough.

515
00:36:07,112 --> 00:36:08,405
And I had something to ask you.

516
00:36:14,870 --> 00:36:16,121
Did it really

517
00:36:18,290 --> 00:36:20,084
mean nothing to you?
Our kiss from that day?

518
00:36:23,337 --> 00:36:26,173
Don't read too much into it.
It was like an accident.

519
00:36:26,256 --> 00:36:28,759
